@Andrzej
Hello, I would love for you can show me where I was being condescending in my comment. It is very common for people to attack the so called "condescending tone" of vegans, so this definitely does not come as a surprise to me. Historically, most social justices movements have been criticized and derided. I wonder, would you consider an abolitionist condescending? Or would you say someone fighting for women's equality is condescending? 
I care about the rights of animals, and if I have offended you with any condescending tone, I apologize. Given you have pangs of guilt and do vegan cooking yourself, you clearly have a strong moral compass. You also say that pigs are smart and playful - yet delicious. According to your logic, if any being is delicious, it is acceptable to eat them, this includes kittens and puppies. I wonder, if another species came along and decided to farm humans, would you find it acceptable to see your loved ones slaughtered because their flesh is "delicious"?

@Johnathan

You seem to be assuming I don't know what you do know, and that I don't think about what I eat, unlike you, and you appear to be trying to educate me. Is that not condescension?

Now you added the absurdly infantile scenario of my human loved ones being slaughtered for food, and added puppies and kittens to the mix, trying to manipulate my emotions, and negating the economic reality of my culture where there is a clear economic divide between farm animals and house pets. That's not how you discuss things seriously. If you think I would be convinced by *that*, that's even more condescension. If you want to be treated like anything else than a proselytizer, stop treating others like they don't know what they are doing, and lose the childish arguments ad absurdum.

